                            <comment id="15859889" author="tjwatson" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2017 17:48:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I fixed this by keeping track of substitutions in the resolver for resources it is resolving.  For resources that have existing wirings I added a new method to FelixResolveContext called getSubstitutionWires so that the resolve doesn&apos;t have to recalculate this in cases where the resolve context already keeps track of it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
